The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Sunday, December 21, 2003 				 LIC premium through Corp Bank ATMs
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Dec. 20: Life Insurance Corporation of India (LIC) and Corporation Bank have joined hands to offer a premium payment facility through the banks ATMs.																								Policyholders who are also ATM cardholders of the bank can avail of this facility, LIC said.																								The premium can be paid during the grace period in any of the ATMs at any time irrespective of the location of the LIC branch to which the policy is attached for servicing, the life insurance major said.																								LIC chairman S. B. Mathur said, We will review this arrangement before we decide to extend this facility to other banks. 																								The facility is a value-added service for the account holders of Corporation Bank, chairman-cum-managing director Cherian Verghese said. ATM cardholders have to register with Corporation Bank giving mandate to debit their premium through their accounts. 
